paper_title: On drawing $K_5$ minus an edge in the plane
abstract: Let K be the graph on vertices \{1, 2, 3, 4, 5\} and all edges except (4, 5). Let f be a general position map of K to the plane. Take the winding numbers of the f-image of the cycle (1, 2, 3) around f(4) and around f(5). If the f-images of non-adjacent edges are disjoint, then the difference of these numbers does not exceed 3.
